name: Tactical Paintball (Canceled)
blurb: Turn based multiplayer tactical strategy game for Android

rewards.reward: A copy of the game. I haven't as of this time figured out exactly how this will be done but it will likely be a special code e-mailed to you that will unlock the full game from the demo. The $2 price is expected to be half off of the expected starting price of $3.99. The lowest price point for the game will be about $1, on sale.
Five copies of the game, for you and your friends.
Ten copies of the game for all of your friends and enemies plus beta access
Ten copies, beta access, & distinguished recognition when you play people online (i.e. different color name, top donator label)

Ten copies, beta access, distinguished recognition, & Be able to design an 'average' player in the draft pool and name them after yourself. Names must look real, be appropriate, and may have to fit into a certain length. So if your last name is, for example, over 20 characters long, it may have to be shortened. If you do not want to use your real name, that is fine as well.

Ten copies, beta access, distinguished recognition, & Be able to design an 'elite' player in the draft pool and name them after yourself. Names must look real, be appropriate, and may have to fit into a certain length. So if your last name is, for example, over 20 characters long, it may have to be shortened. If you do not want to use your real name, that is fine as well.

Ten copies, beta access, distinguished recognition as map designer, an 'elite' player, & and map editor access. The map editor will be written in python (and thus require a PC of some sort to use) and will allow you to create your own maps and scenarios. Your maps and scenarios can be used for personal use. They also can be submitted to be part of the online map rotation or be part of the scenarios other people online can play. Maps are vetted and only a limited number of maps will be part of the rotation at one time. Additionally, if one of your maps makes the rotation, then you'll get that label as well. Names must look real, be appropriate, and may have to fit into a certain length. So if your last name is, for example, over 20 characters long, it may have to be shortened. If you do not want to use your real name, that is fine as well.

Same as $200 but also be able to name a gun, grenade, or certain item that player's will use and see almost every game. You'll get to choose what it is. Possibly have the opportunity to make your own art assets for it as well. Names must look real, be appropriate, and may have to fit into a certain length. So if your last name is, for example, over 20 characters long, it may have to be shortened. If you do not want to use your real name, that is fine as well.
